The paper deals with multiagent systems and game theory, which are central topics in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on bounding the biased price of anarchy in nonatomic routing games, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses diverse populations of agents, which suggests that it may fall under the categories of multiagent systems (cs.MA), networked systems (cs.NI), social and information networks (cs.SI), and machine learning (cs.LG).
